cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for analyzing confocal laser endomicroscopy (CLE) images in neurosurgical imaging. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Neural networks (cs.NE) are also mentioned in the paper as a type of deep learning model used for CLE image analysis. Finally, medical imaging (cs.MM) is a possible category as the paper focuses on the application of CLE in brain tumor surgery.
